अज-शृङ्गी<BR> --This plant (‘goat's horn’), equated by the commentator with Vis2a1n2in (the Odina pinnata), is celebrated as a demon-destroyer in the Atharvaveda. 1) iv. 37. Its other name is Ara1t2aki1. 2) iv. 37, 6. Weber 3) Indische Studien, 18, 144. Cf. Bloomfield, Hymns of the Atharvaveda, 408, 409; Zimmer, Altindisches Leben, 68; Caland, Altindisches Zauberritual, 89. suggests that it is the Prosopis spicigera or Mimosa suma.

