अजात-शत्रु<BR> --He is mentioned as a King of Ka1s4i1 (Ka1s4ya) in the Br2hada1ran2yaka 1) ii. 1, 1. and Kaus2i1taki 2) iv. 1. Upanis2ads, where he instructs the proud Bra1hman2a Ba1la1ki as to the real nature of the self. He is not to be identified with the Aja1tasattu of the Buddhist texts. 3) Cf. Weber, Indische Studien, 1, 213; Hoernle, Osteology, 106; Keith, Zeitschrift der Deutschen Morgenla7ndischen Gesellschaft, 62, 138.

अज्ञातयक्ष्म
