कुयवाच्
कुय-वाच्<BR> (‘evil-speaking’) appears in one passage of the Rigveda 1) i. 174, 7. to denote a demon slain by Indra, probably as a personification of the barbarian opponents of the A1ryans. The expression mr2dhra-va1c (‘speaking insultingly’) is similarly used of barbarians in the Rigveda. 2) v. 29, 10; 32, 8. See Dasyu.

