कुरु<BR> -s4ravan2a Tra1sadasyava is alluded to as dead in a hymn of the Rigveda, 1) x. 33, 4. Cf. Br2haddevata1, vii. 35, 36. which refers also to his son Upamas4ravas, and his father Mitra1tithi. In another hymn 2) x. 32, 9. Cf. Ludwig, Translation of the Rigveda, 3, 165: Geldner, Vediscke Studien, 2, 150, 184; Lanman, Sanskrit Reader, 386. he is mentioned as still alive. His name connects him on the one hand with the Kurus, and on the other with Trasadasyu and the Pu1rus.

