जष<BR> is the name of some aquatic animal or fish in the Atharvaveda 1) xi. 2, 25. There are various readings: jhas2a, jakha, jagha. and the Taittiri1ya Sam2hita1. 2) v. 5, 13, 1. The commentary on the latter text explains it by makara, probably meaning ‘dolphin.’ The word also occurs in the Gopatha Bra1hman2a. 3) ii. 2, 5. Cf. Zimmer, Altindisches Leben, 96; Whitney, Translation of the Atharvaveda, 624 Cf. Jhas2a.

