जीव-गृभ्,<BR> ‘seizing alive,’ is, according to Roth, 1) St Petersburg Dictionary, s.v.; Siebenzig Lieder, 174. the term for a police official in the Rigveda. 2) x. 97, 11. But although this sense is rendered possible by the mention of Madhyamas4i1, perhaps ‘arbitrator,’ in the same passage, 3) Rv. x. 97, 12. it is neither necessary nor probable. 4) Zimmer, Altindisches Leben, 180.

जीवज
जीव-ज<BR> See Jara1yu.

