पाञ्चि,<BR> ‘descendant of Pan5can,’ is the name of a teacher mentioned with disapproval in the S4atapatha Bra1hman2a. 1) i. 2, 5, 9; ii. 1, 4, 27. Cf. Weber, Indische Studien, 1, 434.

पाटव
पाटव,<BR> ‘descendant of Pat2u,’ is a patronymic of Ca1kra in the S4atapatha Bra1hman2a (xii. 8, 1, 17; 9, 3, 1).

पाटा
